    "message_2": "To approximate the value of `y` at `t = 0.2` using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with a step size of `h = 0.1`, we will perform two iterations of the method. Let's denote the function `y' = 2y - 3t + 1` as `f(t, y)`.\n\nFirst iteration (t = 0, y = 1):\n1. k1 = h * f(t, y) = 0.1 * (2 * 1 - 3 * 0 + 1) = 0.1 * 3 = 0.3\n2. k2 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k1/2) = 0.1 * (2 * (1 + 0.3/2) - 3 * (0 + 0.1/2) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.85 = 0.285\n3. k3 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k2/2) = 0.1 * (2 * (1 + 0.285/2) - 3 * (0 + 0.1/2) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.8525 = 0.28525\n4. k4 = h * f(t + h, y + k3) = 0.1 * (2 * (1 + 0.28525) - 3 * (0 + 0.1) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.5705 = 0.25705\n\nNow, update the value of `y`:\ny_new = y + (k1 + 2 * k2 + 2 * k3 + k4) / 6 = 1 + (0.3 + 2 * 0.285 + 2 * 0.28525 + 0.25705) / 6 = 1.28305\n\nSecond iteration (t = 0.1, y = 1.28305):\n1. k1 = h * f(t, y) = 0.1 * (2 * 1.28305 - 3 * 0.1 + 1) = 0.1 * 2.4661 = 0.24661\n2. k2 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k1/2) = 0.1 * (2 * (1.28305 + 0.24661/2) - 3 * (0.1 + 0.1/2) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.339345 = 0.2339345\n3. k3 = h * f(t + h/2, y + k2/2) = 0.1 * (2 * (1.28305 + 0.2339345/2) - 3 * (0.1 + 0.1/2) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.34151725 = 0.234151725\n4. k4 = h * f(t + h, y + k3) = 0.1 * (2 * (1.28305 + 0.234151725) - 3 * (0.1 + 0.1) + 1) = 0.1 * 2.21436345 = 0.221436345\n\nNow, update the value of `y`:\ny_new = y + (k1 + 2 * k2 + 2 * k3 + k4) / 6 = 1.28305 + (0.24661 + 2 * 0.2339345 + 2 * 0.234151725 + 0.221436345) / 6 = 1.566095\n\nTherefore, the approximate value of `y` at `t = 0.2` using the fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with a step size of `h = 0.1` is `y ≈ 1.566095`."
